comments.body:
I attached an example of foo.pq. In case it isn't clear from my description of the problem, it is necessary to make the odbc connection in order to trigger the error. Just reading the parquet file works in both 0.25.3 and 1.0.1. Only when the odbc connection is made does the reading lead to a segfault, and only in pandas 1.0.1. I wrote foo.pq using both 0.25.3 and 1.0.1 and in both cases I saw the segfault in 1.0.1 and not in 0.25.3, long winded way of saying I think it is the read not the write that is the problem. That said, the files do differ:

{noformat}
xbk@499e30e4f63f:~$ diff foo_101.pq foo_25.pq 
Binary files foo_101.pq and foo_25.pq differ
{noformat}
